<p>One would see the â€˜unauthorizedâ€™ keyword in the place of the device name.
<code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">adb shell</code> would also fail stating something about â€˜keys not setâ€™.</p>

<h3 id="solution">Solution</h3>
<ol>
  <li>Unplug your android device from the computer, if it is connected</li>
  <li>Inside your computer:
    <ul>
      <li>Go to <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">$ANDROID_SDK_HOME/platform-tools</code></li>
      <li>Run <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">adb keygen .android/adb_key</code></li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Open your android device</li>
  <li>Go to Settings -&gt; Developer Options</li>
  <li>Touch â€˜Revoke USB debugging authorizationsâ€™</li>
  <li>Plug the device back into the computer</li>
  <li>The device should now ask you for whether to trust this computer. Say yes.</li>
</ol>
